1 Download Ubuntu Server Iso https://ubuntu.com/download/server
2 Create a USB Installation media https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux/blob/main/Creating%20a%20bootable%20USB%20flash%20drive%20with%20an%20image%20writer
3 Setup Ubuntu Server
  If you are on Ubuntu archive mirror configuration Change mirror address from http://id.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ to http://mirror.kku.ac.th/ubuntu/
4 After installation Run sudo nano /etc/os-release
   Then change PREETY_NAME="Ubuntu 26.04 LTS" To PREETY_NAME="Syslack Linux"
   Change NAME="Ubuntu" To NAME="Syslack Linux"
   Change VERSION="26.04 LTS (Resolute Racoon)" To VERSION="1.5" VERSION_ID="26.04" To VERSION_ID="1.5"
   Change VERSION_CODENAME=noble To VERSION_CODENAME=triaxis
   Change ID=ubuntu to ID=syslack
   Remove ID_LIKE=debian
   Change HOME_URL="https://ubuntu.com/" To HOME_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux"
   Change SUPPORT_URL="https://help.ubuntu.com/" To SUPPORT_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux/discussions/3"
   Change BUG_REPORT_URL="https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/" To BUG_REPORT_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux/issues/1"
   Remove PRIVACY_POLICY_URL
   Remove UBUNTU_CODENAME=resolute
5 Run sudo apt install links
  then links https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Syslack-Linux Then find Screenshot from 2026-01-31 16-31-30
   then Save the Screenshot from 2026-01-31 16-31-30 If You See 543212867-3fb3c0d3-784e-46f0-b862-6fd822089d3e.png Change To syslack-logo.png
   then run sudo mv /home/yourusername/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps
   then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo.svg
     sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text.png
     sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text.svg
     sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text-dark.png
     sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text-dark.svg
     Then sudo nano /etc/os-release
     Then Change LOGO=ubuntu-logo To LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png
     Then ctrl x y enter
6 The /etc/os-release Resets when base-files updates. to prevent that, you can mark base-files as held sudo apt-mark hold base-files
7 Remove /etc/update-motd.d with sudo rm -rf /etc/update-motd.d
8 You May Stop The Services Of Snap
   sudo systemctl stop snapd
   sudo systemctl disable snapd

  Purge Snapd (Recommended)
  sudo apt purge snapd

  Clean Up Leftover Directories
  rm -rf ~/snap
  sudo rm -rf /var/snap /var/lib/snapd /var/cache/snapd

  Autoremove
  sudo apt autoremove

  System Updates: Ubuntu may reinstall Snapd during major upgrades. To prevent this, you can block Snapd from being reinstalled:
  sudo apt-mark hold snapd

9 run sudo nano /etc/default/grub
    Change
    GRUB_TIMEOUT=0 To GRUB_TIMEOUT=5 Then GRUB_TIMEOUT_STYLE=hidden to GRUB_TIMEOUT_STYLE=menu
    then Change GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR To GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Syslack Linux"
    Ctrl X Y Enter Then sudo update-grub

10 Change Some Ubuntu To Syslack On /etc/issue on sudo nano /etc/issue If You See Ubuntu 26.04 LTS \n \1 Change it To Syslack Linux \n \1
   Also run sudo nano /etc/issue.net Then Change Ubuntu 26.04 LTS To Syslack Linux

11 links https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux-Archive/blob/main/starfield.png
   then click starfield.png then save
   then run sudo mv /home/yourusername/starfield.png /usr/share/pixmaps
   then run sudo nano /etc/default/grub
   then add GRUB_BACKGROUND="/usr/share/pixmaps/starfield.png"
   then sudo update-grub

12 Install memtest86+ (If you are using Legacy BIOS 64 Bit Hardware) sudo apt install memtest86+ -y

13 Run sudo nano /etc/lsb-release then change
   DISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu
   DISTRIB_RELEASE=26.04
   DISTRIB_CODENAME=resolute
   DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION="Ubuntu 26.04 LTS"

   To

   DISTRIB_ID=Syslack Linux
   DISTRIB_RELEASE=1.5
   DISTRIB_CODENAME=triaxis
   DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION="Syslack Linux"

14 Run sudo apt-mark hold lsb-release
